{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:sirach.31",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 31,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 31 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:1",
      "text": "Watching for riches consumeth the flesh, and the thought thereof driveth away sleep.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:2",
      "text": "The thinking beforehand turneth away the understanding, and a grievous sickness maketh the soul sober.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:3",
      "text": "The rich man hath laboured in gathering riches together, and when he resteth he shall be filled with his goods.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:4",
      "text": "The poor man hath laboured in his low way of life, and in the end he is still poor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:5",
      "text": "He that loveth gold, shall not be justified: and he that followeth after corruption, shall be filled with it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:6",
      "text": "Many have been brought to fall for gold, and the beauty thereof hath been their ruin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:7",
      "text": "Gold is a stumblingblock to them that sacrifice to it: woe to them that eagerly follow after it, and every fool shall perish by it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:8",
      "text": "Blessed is the rich man that is found without blemish: and that hath not gone after gold, nor put his trust in money nor in treasures.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:9",
      "text": "Who is he, and we will praise him? for he hath done wonderful things in his life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:10",
      "text": "Who hath been tried thereby, and made perfect, he shall have glory everlasting. He that could have transgressed, and hath not transgressed: and could do evil things, and hath not done them:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:11",
      "text": "Therefore are his goods established in the Lord, and all the church of the saints shall declare his alms.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:12",
      "text": "Art thou set at a great table? be not the first to open thy mouth upon it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:13",
      "text": "Say not: There are many things which are upon it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:14",
      "text": "Remember that a wicked eye is evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:15",
      "text": "What is created more wicked than an eye? therefore shall it weep over all the face when it shall see.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:16",
      "text": "Stretch not out thy hand first, lest being disgraced with envy thou be put to confusion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:17",
      "text": "Be not hasty in a feast.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:18",
      "text": "Judge of the disposition of thy neighbour by thyself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:19",
      "text": "Use as a frugal man the things that are set before thee: lest if thou eatest much, thou be hated.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:20",
      "text": "Leave off first, for manners' sake: and exceed not, lest thou offend.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:21",
      "text": "And if thou sittest among many, reach not thy hand out first of all, and be not the first to ask for drink.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:22",
      "text": "How sufficient is a little wine for a man well taught, and in sleeping thou shalt not be uneasy with it, and thou shalt feel no pain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:23",
      "text": "Watching, and choler, and gripes, are with an intemperate man:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:24",
      "text": "Sound and wholesome sleep with a moderate man: he shall sleep till morning, and his soul shall be delighted with him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:25",
      "text": "And if thou hast been forced to eat much, arise, go out, and vomit: and it shall refresh thee, and thou shalt not bring sickness upon thy body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:26",
      "text": "Hear me, my son, and despise me not: and in the end thou shalt find my words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:27",
      "text": "In all thy works be quick, and no infirmity shall come to thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:28",
      "text": "The lips of many shall bless him that is liberal of his bread, and the testimony of his truth is faithful.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:29",
      "text": "Against him that is niggardly of his bread, the city will murmur, and the testimony of his niggardliness is true.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:30",
      "text": "Challenge not them that love wine: for wine hath destroyed very many.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:31",
      "text": "Fire trieth hard iron: so wine drunk to excess shall rebuke the hearts of the proud.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:32",
      "text": "Wine taken with sobriety is equal life to men: if thou drink it moderately, thou shalt be sober.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:33",
      "text": "What is his life, who is diminished with wine?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.34",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:34",
      "text": "What taketh away life? death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.35",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:35",
      "text": "Wine was created from the beginning to make men joyful, and not to make them drunk.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.36",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:36",
      "text": "Wine drunken with moderation is the joy of the soul and the heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.37",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:37",
      "text": "Sober drinking is health to soul and body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.38",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:38",
      "text": "Wine drunken with excess raiseth quarrels, and wrath, and many ruins.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.39",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:39",
      "text": "Wine drunken with excess is bitterness of the soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.40",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:40",
      "text": "The heat of drunkenness is the stumblingblock of the fool, lessening strength and causing wounds.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.41",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:41",
      "text": "Rebuke not thy neighbour in a banquet of wine: and despise him not in his mirth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.31.42",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:42",
      "text": "Speak not to him words of reproach: and press him not in demanding again.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
